Package com.cafean.client.values.components

Class AbstractCReal

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.client.values.components.AbstractValue
      • com.cafean.client.values.components.AbstractCReal
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CloneableBlock, Checkable, ComponentElement, ModelElement, java.awt.datatransfer.Transferable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable, javax.swing.undo.StateEditable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CReal, CReal_E
    public abstract class AbstractCReal
extends AbstractValue
implements java.awt.datatransfer.Transferable, java.lang.Comparable, Checkable, CloneableBlock, ComponentElement, javax.swing.undo.StateEditable
    This class provides a replacement for Real (CReal is shorthand for CAFEAN Real). Of particular note: this element is a proper ComponentElement. This allows it to store a foreign-key reference to a user-defined real instead of encoding model and component idents within the value field.

    Any method which returns a CReal attempts to instantiate a new instance of the appropriate type; the calling object determines the returned type. For example, calling multiply on a Length a and a Width b with the call a.multiply(b) returns a new Length object (even though an extension called Area may exist, which would be more appropriate).
